\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Climatology of the AROME simulations (first row), Météo-France stations (second row), the AROME--Station difference (third row), and the relative bias (fourth row), with the spatial correlation between the stations and their closest grid points ($r$), the bias ($ME$ or relative bias $RB$ in bold) and the number of stations compared ($n$). The statistics of the three first columns are derived from daily data from 1959 to 2022. The last column uses hourly data from 1990 to 2022. The contour lines show the 400 and 800\,m elevation isolines. Colour scales are symmetrically saturated. Station markers have uniform size; zero bias is shown as a clearly visible grey fill.}}{12}{figure.caption.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:map_clim}{{3}{12}{Climatology of the AROME simulations (first row), Météo-France stations (second row), the AROME--Station difference (third row), and the relative bias (fourth row), with the spatial correlation between the stations and their closest grid points ($r$), the bias ($ME$ or relative bias $RB$ in bold) and the number of stations compared ($n$). The statistics of the three first columns are derived from daily data from 1959 to 2022. The last column uses hourly data from 1990 to 2022. The contour lines show the 400 and 800\,m elevation isolines. Colour scales are symmetrically saturated. Station markers have uniform size; zero bias is shown as a clearly visible grey fill}{figure.caption.3}{}}
