\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Temporal evolution of the annual mean temperature between 1959 and 2022. For the observations, the time-series are computed from the French thermal indicator, i.e. the mean of a given set of 30 stations with homogenised data, which are the reference temperature stations in France \citep  {gibelin-etal-2014}. For the model, the time-series are computed over the mean of the 30 grid-points that are the closest to the stations. For each time-series, the trend is computed using a linear regression.}}{19}{figure.caption.8}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:trend_tempe}{{8}{19}{Temporal evolution of the annual mean temperature between 1959 and 2022. For the observations, the time-series are computed from the French thermal indicator, i.e. the mean of a given set of 30 stations with homogenised data, which are the reference temperature stations in France \citep {gibelin-etal-2014}. For the model, the time-series are computed over the mean of the 30 grid-points that are the closest to the stations. For each time-series, the trend is computed using a linear regression}{figure.caption.8}{}}
